GIT:
====
Git is a distributed version control system
Git is source code management tool (SCM)
Git is version control system (VCS)
Git is Revision control system (RCS)
=================================================
How to create git local repository :
create a new directory.eg: mkdir my_files
Inside directory give git command "git init" it initalize local repository. 
Eg: cd my_files 
    git init 

Now local git repository is ready to use.
 create files and directories in git 
Files : vim filename
directory : mkdir Directoryname

Add source code to stage area :
git add filename or
git add .
 
commit files in to local repository from stage area

git commit -m "msg" filename

For skippking stage are for commiting files.

git commit -am "msg"

push source code local to remote repository.
 Before pushing you need to configure username & remote repository url
 create a remote repository in github matching with local repository name.

git remote add username <url of git repo>
git push username
=============================================================
How to clone source code from  remote repository  to local machine?
git clone url_of_repository

How to add source code  into stage area?
git add filename 

How to commit source code from stage area to local repository?
git commit -m "msg" filename

How to check changes in files at source area?
git diff filename

How to check changes in files at stage area ?
 git diff --staged flename

How to check changes in file after commiting into local repository?
git show filename

How to restore file after commiting into local repository ?
git checkout commitID^ filename

How to check or get commitid ?
git log 

As per filename
git log filename

As per username
git log --authoer="username" filename
========================================================================




